Tutonium 1.0
_______________________________________________________________

Thank you for your interest in Tutonium.

Tutonium project is licensed under the Apache 2.0 License. 

About:
Tutonium is an extension of the selenium ide, which allows you to 
create webbased tutorials.

Install:
To run Tutonium you need firefox and the selenium ide plug-in. 
After unpacking the tutonium.xpi file just open it with firefox 
and click on the install button. After restarting firefox you will 
find tutonium in your selenium ide plug-in.


Usage:
To create a tutorial you need do build test cases. Each case represents 
a task (tab) in the tutorial. First you have to discribe the task. Use 
selenium command storeText and put some text into the value field.

Tutonium gives you the opportunity to check solutions. Commands like 
verifyElementPresent, verifyTextPresent, verifyText, verifyLocation and 
verifyPath enables tutonium's checking function. Furthermore you have the 
chance to display a help. The clickAndWait command enables tutonium's 
helper function.

Examples and a more detailed manual are attach to the archive file.